				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Tested some other weapons, <span style="font-style: italic">Gnoll Hide Lariat</span>, snare dagger, tash stick, equips them ALL....
<br />

<br />
ALL except <span style="font-style: italic">Di`zok Oracle Shillelagh</span>.
<br />

<br />
What a bunch of cowards, can't even face their own customers, the people that <span style="text-decoration: underline">pay their salaries</span>.
<br />

<br />
They read the forums and <span style="text-decoration: underline">ignore</span> the very important issues that mages have, and do nothing about them, do not even reply, but they do have time to nerf one thing that made our lives a little easier.
<br />

<br />
They gave us <span style="font-style: italic">Persistant Minion</span> and in less than a week nerfed it twice.  First, the invisibility thing makes it less valuable, <span style="text-decoration: underline">after</span> a whole lot of mages paid the 7 AA.  Second, they made keeping an equipped pet less valuable by specifically prohibiting a favorite pet weapon.
<br />

<br />
That, combined the <span style="font-style: italic">"upgraded summoned pet weapons"</span> that cost many runes for no advantage shows that <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span> cares little or nothing for their mage customers.
<br />

<br />
Oh, I am so tempted to use profanity here.
<br />

<br />
I have not decided to cancel my account <span style="text-decoration: underline">yet</span>, but am considering it, but I will tell you one thing.
<br />

<br />
I will never, ever, ever post <span style="text-decoration: underline">any</span> mage techniques or analysis.  <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span> simply cannot be trusted to read public message boards.  If you want my analysis, send tells.
<br />

<br />
Oh, and thank <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span> for ruining a mage community resource.  What is the point of discussing anything, if they are lurking in the background, waiting to nerf it?
<br />

