				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody"></span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">* How can mages determine if a weapon will be equipped?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">So far as I can tell, experimentation.  Once it failed to equip <span style="font-style: italic">DOS</span> I collected a small pile of other pet weapons, <span style="font-style: italic">Gnoll Hide Lariat</span>, and so on, and tested those.  Snare daggers worked, so did tash sticks, just not slow stick.</span><table width="90%" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="3" border="0" align="center"><tr> 	  <td><span class="genmed"><b>Quote:</b></span></td>	</tr>	<tr>	  <td class="quote">* What was the reasoning behind the change?</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">THAT is easy to answer.  It is clear now that <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span> trolls the class boards reading up on the latest tactics.  If they find an unanticipated tactic they do not approve of, they nerf it, without analyzing to determine if said tactic is overpowering, and not communicating before the fact.
<br />

<br />
In fact, expect a number of weapons to go on the prohibited list, now that they have the code for it.  I will not name any for the obvious reason.
<br />

<br />
You know what makes me absolutely <span style="text-decoration: underline">sick</span> about this?  I really enjoy teaching and communicating.  I analyze and summarize what I have learned, and enjoy sharing it with others.
<br />

<br />
But because of <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span>'s cowardly behavior, I have lost this very important part of the enjoyment of the game.  I can no longer be a teacher here.
<br />

<br />
Consider the following.
<br />

<br />
I posted a detailed analysis of rods of transvergence, which was nerfed shortly thereafter.
<br />

<br />
I posted a detailed analysis of reclaiming pets for mana, which was nerfed shortly thereafter.
<br />

<br />
I posted my results with the <span style="font-style: italic">Di`zok Oracle Shillelagh</span>, which was nerfed shortly thereafter.
<br />

<br />
Makes me sick to my stomach to think that the joy I get from being a teacher has been perverted by <span style="font-style: italic">Sony</span> into a weapon.
<br />

<br />
Well, you needed worry about that any more.  I will no longer be sharing information or analysis in this or any other public forum.
<br />

